    • AvailableExpression

      public Boolean AvailableExpression(ServiceRequest serviceRequest)
      Applies a block to return whether the operation should be available based on the current state of the service request. By default, returns true.
      Note: all operations are automatically unavailable on a service request that has been promoted, regardless of the value of this expression.

    • AvailableExpression

      public Boolean AvailableExpression(ServiceRequest serviceRequest, ServiceRequestOperationContext operationContext)
      Applies a block to return whether the operation should be available based on the current state of the service request. By default, returns true.
      Note: all operations are automatically unavailable on a service request that has been promoted, regardless of the value of this expression.

    • AvailableToSpecialistExpression

      public Boolean AvailableToSpecialistExpression(ServiceRequest serviceRequest)
      Applies a block to return whether the operation should be available to specialists when AvailableExpression also evaluates to true; an operation is never available when AvailableExpression is false, regardless of the value of this expression; a specialist will usually perform operations through the ServiceRequestAPI webservice. By default, returns true.

    • AvailableToSpecialistExpression

      public Boolean AvailableToSpecialistExpression(ServiceRequest serviceRequest, ServiceRequestOperationContext operationContext)
      Applies a block to return whether the operation should be available to specialists when AvailableExpression also evaluates to true; an operation is never available when AvailableExpression is false, regardless of the value of this expression; a specialist will usually perform operations through the ServiceRequestAPI webservice. By default, returns true.

      public String DescriptionExpression(ServiceRequest serviceRequest, ServiceRequestOperationContext operationContext)
      Applies a block to return the message that will appear in the service request history event generated by invoice.performOperation. By default, returns the display name of service request operation being performed, which is automatically set on the ServiceRequestOperationContext instance.
